<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If you set an id on a display group, the id will not be honored. For example:</p>

<p>$group = new Zend_Form_DisplayGroup('foo', new Zend_Loader_PluginLoader);
 $group-&gt;setAttrib('id','bar');
 echo $group-&gt;getId();  // prints 'foo'</p>

<p>The bug lies in Zend_Form_DisplayGroup::getId(). The getId() method checks a non-existent instance member 'id'. It should check for an id element in the attribs member instead.</p>

